Preheat oven to 200°C. Boil the #kettle{} for water to use for the couscous. Cut each
@halloumi{250%g} block into eight slices. Cut the @apple{1} into quarters and remove
any core, then chop into 1cm wide slices.

Lightly oil a #baking tray{}, then lay the halloumi and apple slices on top. Drizzle
over a little more oil. Roast on the top shelf of the oven until the halloumi is
golden and the apple softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @couscous{150%g} and @vegetable stock powder{1/2%pot} in a large
#bowl{}. Pour the @water{700%ml} into the bowl and stir to dissolve the stock. Mix
in the @baby spinach{125%g} and cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side
for ~{10%minutes}.

In the meantime, roughly chop the @walnuts{20} and @flat leaf parsley{1}. Pop in a
bowl, add a glug of oil and the @pomegranate seeds{80}. Set aside.

Once the couscous is ready, add half of the salsa to the bowl of couscous. Mix well,
then season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Once everything is done,
tidy up. Prepare your plates and a grab glass of wine!

Spoon the couscous into bowls and lay the halloumi and apple on top. Spoon the
remaining pomegranate walnut salsa on top and devour!